Arsenal playmaker, Mesut Ozil has said that the Gunners were not very pretty against West Ham United following their 1-0 Premier League victory on Saturday. Alexandre Lacazette scored the only goal of the match for Mikel Arteta’s side following an assist from Mesut Ozil. In a tweet on his official twitter page after the match, the ex-Germany international said the victory against the visitors was a must win. He wrote: “3 PL victories on the bounce. “Wasn’t very pretty today, but a must win game, so we’ll take that! Smiling face with sunglasses #YaGunnersYa #M1Ö.” Arsenal’s next Premier League fixture is against Brighton next weekend.